Package: pigauto
Title: Phylogenetic Imputation via Graph Autoencoders
Version: 0.3.0
Authors@R:
    person("Shinichi", "Nakagawa", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "itchyshin@gmail.com")
Description: Imputes missing species trait data using a Residual Phylogenetic
    Denoising Autoencoder (ResidualPhyloDAE) that combines Brownian-Motion
    phylogenetic imputation (via Rphylopars) with an attention-based graph
    neural network. Features validation-calibrated per-trait gates to prevent
    GNN overshoot, conformal prediction intervals with guaranteed coverage,
    phylogenetic label propagation for discrete traits, and adaptive spectral
    encoding that scales with tree size. Supports continuous, binary,
    categorical, ordinal, and count traits in a unified latent space, with
    optional multiple observations per species. Includes a 300-species AVONET
    bird morphology subset and a matching BirdTree phylogeny.
